  "prompt": "My H1b visa is under Admin processing for about a year now, and there's has been no update so far. What options do I have?",
  "response": "I'm not a legal expert, but if your H-1B visa application has been under administrative processing for a long time (like a year), here are some general options you might consider:\n\n1. **Reach Out for Updates**: Contact the consulate or embassy that is processing your visa to inquire about the status. Sometimes, a direct inquiry can yield some information about what the holdup might be.\n\n2. **Consult an Immigration Attorney**: It might be beneficial to consult with a qualified immigration attorney. They can provide specific advice based on your situation and help you understand your rights, options, and any potential next steps.\n\n3. **Check Your Case Status**: If you haven't already, you should check the online status of your H-1B petition on the USCIS website. This can provide additional information.\n\n4. **Consider Other Visa Options**: Depending on your circumstances, you might want to explore other visa categories you may qualify for.\n\n5. **Request a Congressional Inquiry**: In some cases, you can ask your local congressional representative to inquire about the status of your visa application. They may be able to get more information from the embassy or consulate.\n\n6. **Stay Informed**: Keep yourself updated on any changes to immigration laws or policies that might affect your situation.\n\n7. **Plan for Alternatives**: If your application continues to be delayed, it might be worth exploring potential alternative immigration pathways or considering returning to your home country until your situation is resolved.\n\n8. **Maintain Legal Status**: Ensure that you maintain lawful status in the U.S. if you're currently in the country. Overstaying your visa or being out of status can impact future immigration opportunities.\n\nConsider all these options and choose the ones that best align with your situation. Good luck!",
